{
  "local_port": 34376,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with your **UAN (Universal Account Number)**, follow these steps:\n\n### **1. Prerequisites**\n   - You must have your **UAN number**.\n   - Your mobile number should be active and not already linked to another UAN.\n   - Ensure your Aadhaar is linked with your UAN (if applicable).\n\n### **2. Online Method (via EPFO Portal)**\n   - **Step 1:** Visit the **EPFO Member Portal**: [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in)\n   - **Step 2:** Log in using your **UAN** and **password**. If you don't have a password, click on \"**Forgot Password**\" and reset it using your registered mobile number or Aadhaar.\n   - **Step 3:** On the dashboard, go to the \"**Manage**\" section and select \"**Contact Details**\".\n   - **Step 4:** Update your mobile number and click \"**Save**\". An OTP will be sent to your new mobile number for verification.\n   - **Step 5:** Enter the OTP and submit the details. Your mobile number will be updated.\n\n### **3. Offline Method (via Employer)**\n   - Submit a request to your **employer** to update your mobile number in the **EPFO records**.\n   - Your employer will update the details through their **EPFO portal**, and you will receive a confirmation once the update is done.\n\n### **4. Verify the Update**\n   - After updating, log in to the EPFO portal again to ensure your mobile number is displayed correctly.\n   - You can also opt to receive SMS alerts from EPFO to confirm the update.\n\n### **Important Notes**\n   - Only **one mobile number** can be linked to one UAN.\n   - Ensure your **Aadhaar** is linked to your UAN for seamless updates.\n   - If you face issues, contact the **EPFO helpline** (Toll-Free: 1800-118-005) or visit the nearest EPFO office.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully register or update your mobile number with your UAN.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
